As Mzansi entered the first day of level four lockdown a number of people have been bust. On Friday Police Minister, Bheki Cele and Gauteng MEC of Community Safety, Faith Mazibuko led a joint lockdown operation around Krugersdorp as well as the N12 highway near Carletonville. These included roadblocks, spaza shops raids as well as random stop and searches.  A number of people were found in possession of drugs and booze. Cele expressed disappointment that people were still undermining lockdown regulations, when covid-19 continues to claim lives. He said South Africans have been misbehaving.